@title "Furthermore, the coordination of body movements may continue even after the verbal-verbal coordination between interactants deteriorates. Rutter and Stephenson (1977) found that even when conversation was sometimes disrupted with various types of speech disturbances (interruptions, simultaneous speech, and pauses), the degree of interpersonal coordination apparent in the nonverbal behaviors of the interactants continued unabated."
